ml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:595:"<p>I&#8217;ve been working on a javascript plugin that creates a mask over a site and it really got me thinking about how we use z-index. Most of the time, we&#8217;re making things more complicated than they really need to be. In the past, when working on a popup I would just drop this in the...  <a href="http://themble.com/keeping-your-z-index-in-check/" title="Read Keeping your z-index in check">Read more &#187;</a></p><p>The post <a href="http://themble.com/keeping-your-z-index-in-check/">Keeping your z-index in check</a> appeared first on <a href="http://themble.com">Themble</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"eddiemachado";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1864:"<p>I&#8217;ve been working on a javascript plugin that creates a mask over a site and it really got me thinking about how we use z-index. Most of the time, we&#8217;re making things more complicated than they really need to be.</p>\n<p>In the past, when working on a popup I would just drop this in the CSS and not think twice:</p>\n<pre>\r\n.popup {\r\n  position: absolute;\r\n  z-index: 9999;\r\n}\r\n</pre>\n<p>Thinking about it though, it&#8217;s crazy how I just went from 0 to 9999 without thinking about it. <strong>A z-index of 3, 4, or 5 would have done the same job without an issue.</strong> In fact, simply putting <span>position: relative or absolute</span> will solve a ton of your positioning issues. So, if you use a few z-index values to move things around a bit, you&#8217;ll really only need to go as high as the teens or mid-twenties. Yet, <strong>z-index: 9999</strong> is used all over the place. This means for tools like popups or things that <strong>have</strong> to be in front of everything, developers have to use crazy numbers like <em>z-index: 1000000</em> to be <strong>sure</strong> that their element is always on top.</p>\n<p>So, let&#8217;s make the lives of developers (and our users) easier, <strong>don&#8217;t use z-index: 9999;</strong>. Try something like 50 or even 100 if you want to be sure.</p>\n<h3>Bonus!</h3>\n<p>A made a nice little mockup with some basic info on positioning. <a href="http://codepen.io/eddiemachado/full/ynmbi">Check it out on Codepen.io</a>.</p>\n<div class="alert info">\n<p><strong>Fun Fact:</strong> The highest possible value allowed in z-index is 2147483647. <a href="http://softwareas.com/whats-the-maximum-z-index">Source</a></p>\n</div>\n<p>The post <a href="http://themble.com/keeping-your-z-index-in-check/">Keeping your z-index in check</a> appeared first on <a href="http://themble.com">Themble</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:54:"http://themble.com/keeping-your-z-index-in-check/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"Holy Whitespace";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"http://themble.com/holy-whitespace/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";