(419, 1, '2013-10-16 14:10:50', '2013-10-16 12:10:50', '<p>Registered industrial psychologist Leezlle Kotz has worked in the HR field since 1999, holding senior positions at among others The Foschini Group and The Shoprite Group of Companies. She has also consulted for among others Capitec Bank, BHP Billiton, Woolworths, Tiger Brands, Meatco and Stellenbosch University.</p>\r\n\r\n                    <p>Her areas of expertise include talent management, leadership development, competency frameworks, recruitment and selection, talent assessment, coaching and team facilitation.</p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>Work Experience</h2>\r\n                    <p>In 2012 Leez&eacute;lle launched TALL Consulting, a company that offers a range of talent and leadership services such as talent management, leadership development, coaching and team interventions.</p>\r\n\r\n                    <p>Before this she worked for various large corporations, including The Foschini Group, where she was senior HR manager: group resourcing and responsible for the development and implementation of the groups recruitment strategy and assessment philosophy.</p>\r\n\r\n                    <p>She was also resource manager at The Shoprite Group for four years, where her portfolio included strategy development, group talent management, recruitment and selection, and employment equity policy development and implementation.</p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>At OIM</h2>\r\n                    <p>Leezlle first joined OIM in 2004 as a leadership and performance improvement consultant. During her four-year stint at the company her client list included Meatco and Hangana Seafood (both in Namibia), Woolworths, Tiger Brands and Barloworld where she designed, among other, material for various leadership development programmes and was involved in change management, coaching, diversity training, competency profiling and leadership assessments.</p>\r\n\r\n                    <p>She rejoined OIM in 2013, this time as managing director of the Leadership Talent division which focuses on a range of offerings that help organisations to define, assess, develop and manage their leadership talent in an integrated way.</p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>Qualifications</h2>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                    <ul>\r\n                        <li>Currently doing a PhD in consulting psychology through Unisa</li>\r\n                        <li>MA in Industrial Psychology from Stellenbosch University (2004)</li>\r\n                        <li>She served as chairperson of the Western Cape branch of the Society for Industrial & Organisational Psychology of SA in 2006 and 2007</li>\r\n                    </ul>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>Leez&eacute;lle is an accredited facilitator for numerous industrial psychology tools, including:</p>\r\n                    <ul>\r\n                        <li>Insights&reg;</li>\r\n                        <li>Career Path Appreciation (CPA) (Bioss)</li>\r\n                        <li>IRIS Trained (2003) (Bioss)</li>\r\n                        <li>MBTI Step I and II (Jopie van Rooyen)</li>\r\n                        <li>OPQ (SHL)</li>\r\n                        <li>15FQ+ (Psytech)</li>\r\n                        <li>Cognitive assessments (Psytech, SHL)</li>\r\n                        <li>WPS (SHL)</li>\r\n                    </ul>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>On A Personal Note</h2>\r\n                    <p>When Leez&eacute;lle is not having tea parties with her toddler daughter she enjoys waterskiing and taking her off-road motorcycle for a spin. But when she really wants to get away from it all she, her husband and daughter head for a remote camping site where there is no cellphone reception.</p>', 'Leezlle Kotz', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'leezlle-kotzeacute', '', '', '2013-10-22 16:23:36', '2013-10-22 14:23:36', '', 0, 'http://staging.fishgate.co.za/OIM/?post_type=team_members&#038;p=419', 3, 'team_members', '', 0),
